    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Of Manners and Attire</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Carl Faith letter comments on July 22 letters on manners (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I was amused by the July 22 letters about manners. People in Princeton, N.J., where I live, eat in restaurants dressed in muscle shirts, miniskirts, sweatshirts, tennis shorts and gym shoes. Taste is out, tacky in.</p>
        <p>In such circumstances, who can blame me for keeping my Shakespearean baldness covered, to ward off the arctic flows of overhead wind shafts?</p>
        <p>CARL FAITH  Princeton, N.J., July 24, 2000</p>
      </block>
